original: Bergquist, Febe Emmy Isabella, läroverksadjunkt, Halmstad, f. 14/5/94 i Hjärtlanda, Jönköp. L, av kontr :prost. Fingal B. o. Anna Östberg. — Stud:-ex. 13, fil. kand. i Lund 16, fil. mag. 17, efterpr. 26 o. 29. Res. t. Tyskl. 14, 21, 22, 23 o. 29, t. Engl. 20, 25 o. 27, Frankr. 31, 32, 36 o. 38, Danm. 18. Lär. v. Solbacka 18, i Vara 19, i Lysekil 19, guvernant i Engl. 20, lär. v. S. Rudebecks sk. o. gymn. f. fl. i Gbg 21-30, ämneslär :a i tyska, eng. o. franska v. Halmstads h. a. 1. 29, adj. i tyska o. franska där sed. 41.
translated:
Bergquist, Febe Emmy Isabella was a high school teacher in Halmstad. She was born on May 14th, 1894 in Hjärtlanda, Jönköping County to the parish priest Fingal B. Bergquist and Anna Östberg. Febe passed her studentexamen (the final exam in Swedish secondary school) in 1913, earned a Bachelor of Arts degree in Lund in 1916, and a Master of Arts degree in 1917. She took supplementary courses in 1926 and 1929 and traveled to Germany in 1914, 1921, 1922, 1923 and 1929, England in 1920, 1925, and 1927, France in 1931, 1932, 1936 and 1938, and Denmark in 1918.

Febe worked as a teacher in Solbacka in 1918, Vara in 1919, Lysekil in 1919, governess in England in 1920, and as a teacher at several schools in Gothenburg between 1921-1930. She taught German, English, and French at Halmstad högre allmänna läroverk (a type of high school) from 1929, becoming an adjunct teacher in German and French in 1941. She was married but no information is provided on when she married or to whom.
